flowRoot.flowPara: Fill in the lines with names of regulatory mechanisms, government organizations and other things which exert authority. Then use the model to the side to figure out what kind of relations they regulate.
This can help to determine which have infrastructural implications and which have other roles, as well as just being very fascinating.

Political governors are high level political authorities. These are people whose obligations have to do with management of the social structure at large. Includes kings, presidents, bureaucrats, clergy, etc.
Economic governors are the owners of the means of production. These have the capital and investment capacity to acquire and use resources and so on market products.

Political forces are those who maintain the existing political doctrine. This is primarily those who enforce the state monopoly on violence, but can also be information services such as media, education, clergy and otherwise, depending on the social structure. They will commonly but not always answer to political governors and directly or indirectly effect their will. [This was missing from Marx's original analysis]

Economic forces are those who produce the goods necessary to society (and also the unnecessary goods). These are commonly refered to as labor or workforce, regardless of whether it implies skilled or unskilled work.
